\subsubsection{Reading Guide}
\vspace{-0.4cm}
The report is structured in three sections. In each section different aspects of the project will be analysed.
\vspace{-0.8cm}
\begin{itemize}
\item \ref{part:part1} Problem Analysis 
\item \ref{part:part2} Technical Solution
\item \ref{part:part3} Discussion 
\end{itemize}
\vspace{-0.2cm}
The Problem Analysis will be dealing with the surrounding environment and thereby contain the fundamental discussions for a Requirement Specification, which in the end results in guidelines and instructions for The Technical Solution. The Technical Solution contains design considerations and solutions to the issues discussed. The Discussion part contains a summary, discussion and reflection regarding the obtained solutions.

